HEADWORD: colubrid
<hw>colubrid</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any member of a large family
(<fam>Colubridae</fam>) of mostly harmless temperate-to-tropical
terrestrial or arboreal or aquatic snakes.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> colubrid snake.</syn>⟦br⟧
